- 'Top 5 industries' refers to the industries with the highest average stock market index values;
- 'Recent performance' includes the average, maximum, and minimum index values, as well as the count of index entries;
- 'Alert status' indicates the most recent alert message and date for each industry, or a message stating there were no alerts in the last 7 days.

- "Recent alerts" refer to alerts created within the last month;
- "User preferences" include the industry ID, alert type, and threshold value;
- "Industry names" are provided by joining the `industries` table;
- "Notifications from a garden of industries" is a metaphorical way to describe alerts related to different industries, where each user has their own set of interests or "plants" in the garden.

- "Accident & Health Insurance" is a specific industry within the financial sector;
- "Validated index value" refers to the sum of index values that have been marked as validated;
- "Sector average index value" is the average index value of all industries within the same sector as "Accident & Health Insurance";
- "Trend analysis" reports provide insights into market trends and performance over time.

- 'blossomed' refers to industries that have shown strong performance;
- 'validated data' means the index values have been confirmed for accuracy;
- 'average stock market index value' is the mean value of the stock market index for a given industry over the specified period.

- "High-performance indices" refer to those with a value greater than 100;
- "High-performance rate" is the average of industries where more than 75% of indices are high-performance;
- "User preferences" indicate the industries a user is interested in;
- "Latest index value" is the most recent index value for each industry.

- The user ID `1` refers to a specific user in the system;
- "Performance metrics" include average, maximum, and minimum index values, as well as the count of index entries for each industry;
- "User preferences" include the alert type and threshold set by the user for each industry.

- 'Significant waves of price changes' refers to the threshold value for triggering alerts being greater than 3.0;
- 'Shared with the community' means the reports have been marked as shared (`is_shared = 1`);
- The time frame 'during the year 2021' refers to the date range from '2021-01-01' to '2021-12-31'.

- "Stock market heartbeat" refers to the stock market index value, which is a measure of the performance of a particular segment of the stock market;
- "Latest pulse" refers to the most recent date when the index value was recorded;
- "Audience's interests have illuminated" means that there are active user preferences indicating interest in the industry.

- "Top 5 sectors" refers to the industries with the highest average stock market index values;
- "Robust growth" refers to high average index values over all recorded dates;
- "Recent performances" refers to the most recent validated index values within the last year.

- "Recent activity" includes both alerts and reports, and the last activity time is the most recent timestamp from either;
- "User preferences" include the industry they are interested in, the type of alert, and the threshold value;
- "Alerts" are notifications triggered by specific conditions, such as market changes or price movements.

- The "pulse of each industry" refers to the average, maximum, and minimum stock market index values;
- "Weaving together the weave of performance metrics" means combining industry performance data;
- "Threads of user interests" refer to user preferences and alert types;
- "Recent alarms of market alerts" are the alerts triggered in the past month;
- "Footprints of user activity" include logins, data accesses, and report generations;
- "Paint a picture" implies presenting a comprehensive overview of the data.

- "Stock market index" is a statistical measure of the performance of a group of stocks representing a segment of the market or the entire market;
- "Threshold" in the context of user preferences refers to a specific value that, when exceeded or not met by the stock market index, triggers an alert;
- "Alerts" are notifications sent to users when their specified conditions for the stock market index are met;
- "Industry" refers to a specific sector of the economy, such as technology, healthcare, or finance.
